Vanguard hosts the Central Bank of Nigeria, CBN, with the Bankers’ Committee to thinker on economic growth. The Bankers’ Committee has resolved to sustain the momentum of the Central Bank of Nigeria’s (CBN) on-going collaborative process with it (the committee) to actualise its objective of ensuring the financial sector contribution to the social economic development of the country. December 7, 2010 In "Business" The Bankers’ Committee has reiterated the strategic importance of the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprise (MSMEs) to the growth of the nation’s economy. This was stated at a workshop in Abuja on the N220 billion Micro, Small & Medium Enterprise Development Fund organised by the Bankers’ Committee’s sub-committee on Economic… September 28, 2015 In "Business" The Bankers Committee said that banks will contribute about N30 billion of their profit after tax in a newly created Agriculture/Small and Medium Enterprises, SME, fund, designed to support the funding and access to finance by SMEs and primary agriculture. December 12, 2016 In "News"